![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/63301572-c6a8-4c83-8c90-1c0161b67afe/20240807_171623.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_MJF DEF. KYLE FLETCHER_**
    

Fletcher and MJF opened Dynamite with a very solid match. Towards the end, Don Callis gives Fletcher a screwdriver but Fletcher refused to use it. MJF low blows Fletcher for the win.

After the match, MJF takes out the ref, then he takes out Kyle Fletcher with the Dynamite Diamond Ring. MJF says he's going to do what Ospreay won't.

MJF is going to give Kyle Fletcher a Tiger Driver 91 when we're shown Will Ospreay escaping a locked room.

Ospreay stops MJF but Fletcher is out. Don Callis blames Ospreay for not getting there fast enough

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f8d37e87-6661-40d3-bd2c-be059ccf0abf/20240807_173714.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_MARIAH MAY DEF. VIVA VAN_**
    

Mariah handles Viva Van fairly easily. She's given a gift after the match and it's a photo of Toni holding her. Mariah mocks this photo but she doesn't see the message on the back until it's too late.

Toni Storm attacks and they're brawling again. The hatred will not end between these two until Wembley.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0a1b54b7-174c-4f20-90c4-e49d164da7ea/20240807_173715.jpg?format=original)

